# 2. ピクニックに行こう！

Mizuki: *Sigh* (I got home way later than I was hoping to... I still have to keep editing the music video from where I left off yesterday too...)
Mizuki: (Hm? Ena's calling me...?)
Mizuki: Heya! What's up?
Ena: <Um, Mizuki, there's something I'd like to ask you...>
Ena: <If you're free next Saturday, how would you feel about going on a picnic?>
Mizuki: <A picnic? That's rare coming from someone who hates going outside as much as you do. What's going on?>
Ena: <I was invited to go, and I thought a change of pace might be nice.>
Ena: <My idol friends are the ones that asked me to go. You know, the ones I talked about before?>
Mizuki: <Yeah! Airi Momoi, right?! It's pretty cool that you're really friends with actual idols.>
Ena: <I just happened to meet her in junior high and we've been friends since. Oh, this other girl from Airi's group, Shizuku Hinomori, is also coming.>
Mizuki: <What?! Shizuku Hinomori as in THE Shizuku Hinomori?!>
Mizuki: <Wait, Mafuyu mentioned before that they go to the same school. Talk about a small world...!>
Ena: <I met her for the first time the other day too. She seemed nice and pretty laid-back, but I doubt she's ever crossed paths with Mafuyu...>
Ena: <I mentioned you to them too and they said they'd like to meet you. How about it?>
Mizuki: <Seriously?! I totally want to meet them...!>
Mizuki: (But if I can't tell anyone about myself, how can I ever really be friends with them...?)
Mizuki: <Actually, nevermind... I think I'll pass, sorry...>
Mizuki: <I just remembered that I might have to work around that time next week.>
Ena: <"Might?" That means you're not actually scheduled to yet, right...?>
Mizuki: <Yeah, but... It'd be their first time meeting me, and we might not have anything in common or a lot to talk about so...>
Ena: <We're talking about idols here. It's their job to make people they meet for the first time feel welcome.>
Ena: <And you're the one that's always talking about getting different perspectives on things. Seeing a pretty landscape might even give you some ideas for the video, you know?>
Mizuki: <Hmm... You might be right... But why do you want me to go so much? Did something happen?>
Ena: <Hey, stay on topic. I'm the one that's asking you if you want to come on this picnic.>
Mizuki: <Well...>
Mizuki: (She's really coming after me today. She'll probably start asking more questions if I'm not careful...)
Mizuki: <Okay, if you're gonna be that insistent, I'll go...>
Ena: <Yes, finally...!>
Ena: <The plan's to take a tour on a bus. We have to register as a group and stuff, so I'll send you more info about it later.>
Mizuki: <Got it. I can't wait!>
Ena: <Good. We'll talk again later.>
Mizuki: <Alright, later!!>
Mizuki: (A picnic with Hinomori and Momoi does sound like fun, but...)
Mizuki: ...
Luka: You've improved so much, Shizuku. Your last turn there looked perfect too.
Shizuku: Thank you! It's all because you taught me so well, Luka. Oh, these footsteps must be...
Airi: Hey, you two!
Shizuku: Airi!
Luka: Welcome, Airi. I heard from Shizuku that you wouldn't be able to make it today because of club activities.
Airi: We ended earlier than expected. Looks like I made it just in time too.
Airi: By the way, Shizuku, I just heard back from Ena. She said Akiyama's gonna come with us!
Shizuku: Really? That's wonderful. I hope our little trip can help Akiyama feel a little better...
Airi: Yeah. It's pretty rare for Ena to worry about someone this much, so I want to help her out too.
Luka: Oh, are you going somewhere together?
Shizuku: We are. Airi, a couple of her friends and I are going to the highlands to have a little picnic.
Luka: A picnic in the highlands? That sounds lovely! I'm sure it's going to be very beautiful...
Shizuku: I hope so too. I went quite some time ago as part of a shoot for an educational TV program, so I can't wait to go again.
Airi: Oh, that show? Whoever edited that deserves an award. I was on the edge of my seat because you were being so clumsy that time...
Shizuku: I never knew it was so hard to tie knots and start campfires... Still, I had quite a bit of fun.
Shizuku: But that was then. I just hope we all get to have as much fun as possible...!
Luka: Hehe. I'm sure it'll be a wonderful picnic♪
Shizuku: Oh, Luka...! Would you like to come as well?
Airi: Yeah, you actually could if you jump onto one of our phones and have us carry you around!
Luka: Oh, you would do that for me?
Shizuku: Yes, of course! The hiking course is supposed to take quite a bit of time, so you should be able to take a look around as well.
Luka: Thanks, you two. If you don't mind, I'd like to join you.
Shizuku: I'm glad you are. You being there will make our picnic just that much more fun, Luka.
Airi: Then I'll have to whip up and bring a special lunch for us to share too!
Mizuki: Whoa, it's the real deal! Airi Momoi and Shizuku Hinomori in the flesh!
Shizuku: Hehe. Thank you for joining us today, Akiyama.
Airi: Yeah, sorry for just dropping this on you, but we're glad you came.
Mizuki: No, I should be the one thanking you two. Hehe. I even ended up wearing my favorite outfit today♪
Mizuki: Ena, they're really here! People you see on TV or in magazines! They're sooo cute too!
Ena: Okay, Mizuki, calm down. Also, keep it down...!
Airi: Hehe. We should be fine with this many people around. I'm glad we're doing this, Shizuku.
Shizuku: Me too! I'm happy that Shinonome's friend is already enjoying everything so much.
Airi: Oh, also... Calling only you by your last name seems a bit strange, so mind if we call you "Mizuki" instead?
Shizuku: Yes, I'd like that too. Please, feel free to call us by our first names as well.
Mizuki: Wait, really? I can't say no to that♪ Thanks for having me today, Airi, Shizuku!
Shizuku: You too, Shinonome...
Ena: Me? Oh, right... We have been calling each other by our last names. In that case, thank you for having me too, Shizuku.
Shizuku: You're very welcome! Let's have ourselves a fun picnic today, Ena!
Mizuki: Yeah! Thank you so much for doing this, Ena!
Ena: Yes, yes, you're very welcome.
Ena: Airi, shouldn't the bus already be here? Maybe we should get going.
Airi: Yeah. We're still a little early, but that might be a good idea.
Shizuku: Um, Airi... Is it just me or does Mizuki seem better than Ena let on?
Airi: Maybe. Mizuki does seem nice and might not be as bothered by whatever Ena was talking about...
Mizuki: Hey, I brought some snacks too! We can all have some while we're on the bus!
Ena: That's great but don't make a mess, okay?
Mizuki: You got it!!
Airi & Shizuku: Hm...?
Nene: He's late...
Nene: (Rui said, "Wait by the station," but now I feel like it would've been better to go to his house to pick him up first...)
Nene: (Oh, that tour bus over there's going to the same place we are...)
Nene: (We decided to take an express train, but a bus might've been easier since we wouldn't have to change trains...)
Nene: (No, today's not about doing things the easy way. Today's all about...)
Rui: Hello, Nene. Sorry for making you wait.
Nene: Rui, there you are. You're late and... What's with the luggage?
Rui: Oh, I brought quite a few things just for today!
Rui: I was happy to hear that you wanted to build up some stamina for our shows.
Rui: But at the same time, I was a little surprised that you'd want to do something like this, Nene.
Nene: W-Well...
Nene: If we want to make it so Phoenix Wonderland doesn't just change in front of our eyes, Rui, we have to keep thinking up new kinds of shows, right?
Nene: I'm hoping that this will help achieve that goal.
Nene: Emu and Tsukasa are way more athletic than I am too. I really don't how I'm the one that's always out of breath in the end.
Rui: Hehe. I understand. We should be doing everything in our power right now.
Rui: I hope you're ready for some high-speed, high-altitude training!!
Nene: High-speed? Even though you're running this late? And why are we going all the way to the highlands to train?
Rui: Because it'll be more fun than just running around here, no? You get to see some beautiful landscapes under a great big sky...!
Rui: And above all else, you won't have to worry about any prying eyes!
Nene: Oh...!
Nene: Don't tell me that you're lugging around some props that you can't test at the Wonder Stage...! Is this why we're going so far out of our way today...?!
Rui: My, would you look at the time! We need to hurry if we're going to catch our train, Nene...!
Nene: Hey, wait...! You don't get to treat me like Tsukasa! I'm not gonna be a guinea pig for your props!!
